ish personal name <i>Olla</i> + Old English <i>ēg</i> ‘island’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":18,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705201,"age":112,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Alice Olney was born in Oxfordshire, England. She had at least 2 sons with William Saunders."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1437–1478":"1437–1478","1450–1494":"1450–1494","–1511":"–1511","–Female":"Surnud","1437":"1437","1511":"1511","1478":"1478","1455":"1455","1450":"1450","1494":"1494","1549":"1549","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, England","Banbury, Oxfordshire, England":"Banbury, Oxfordshire, England"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","1437–1478":"1437–1478","1450–1494":"1450–1494","–1511":"–1511","–Female":"Kuollut","1437":"1437","1511":"1511","1478":"1478","1455":"1455","1450":"1450","1494":"1494","1549":"1549","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, England","Banbury, Oxfordshire, England":"Banbury, Oxfordshire, England"},"fr":{"–":"Décédée","1437–1478":"1437–1478","1450–1494":"1450–1494","–1511":"–1511","–Female":"Décédée","1437":"1437","1511":"1511","1478":"1478","1455":"1455","1450":"1450","1494":"1494","1549":"1549","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, Angleterre","Banbury, Oxfordshire, England":"Banbury, Oxfordshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Alice Olney est née à Oxfordshire, Angleterre. Elle a eu au moins 2 fils avec William Saunders."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","1437–1478":"1437–1478","1450–1494":"1450–1494","–1511":"–1511","–Female":"Verstorben","1437":"1437","1511":"1511","1478":"1478","1455":"1455","1450":"1450","1494":"1494","1549":"1549","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, England","Banbury, Oxfordshire, England":"Banbury, Oxfordshire, England","lifeSummary":"Alice Olney wurde in Oxfordshire, England geboren. Sie hatte mit William Saunders mindestens 2 Söhne."},"ht":{"–":"Desede","1437–1478":"1437–1478","1450–1494":"1450–1494","–1511":"–1511","–Female":"Desede","1437":"1437","1511":"1511","1478":"1478","1455":"1455","1450":"1450","1494":"1494","1549":"1549","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, England","Banbury, Oxfordshire, England":"Banbury, Oxfordshire, England"},